node.text: The road that leads to Roger W. Smith's remote workshop is not so different from the one that leads to Philippe Dufour’s. But while the Swiss can blame tradition for their isolation, this Brit's exile appears to be self-imposed. For the full story, go to https://www.hodinkee.com/articles/episode-1-roger-w-smith

node.text: It’s not often you get to be in the presence of true greatness. And I know on this site we tend to talk up how wonderful this watch is or how revelatory that watch is. We even, at at times, say things like “this is a once-in-a-lifetime” chance to see this or that. And we mean it when we say it, but we are speaking in relative terms, because we are, after all, talking about watches. But today, I'll speak in far more literal terms, because in this special episode of Talking Watches I talk to an actual living legend. In fact, just a few weeks ago in Palm Beach, Florida, I had the honor of sitting down with a man who is the very best in the world at something – someone who remains at the pinnacle of his sport, though his reign ended decades ago. I'm talking about Jack Nicklaus. Yes, the Jack Nicklaus. For the full story, go to https://www.hodinkee.com/articles/talking-watches-with-jack-nicklaus

node.text: Earlier this year, Grand Seiko revealed three new watches in the 9F-powered GMT SBGN series. Each piece comes outfitted with an updated case profile including a ceramic bezel and radial dial finish. The SBGN019 and SBGN021 are standard releases, while the SBGN023 is a limited edition celebrating the Seiko family's 140th anniversary. All three can be found now in the H Shop.

Cara Barrett (@its.cara.time): HODINKEE alum, watch expert, turtleneck sweater style icon (see Talking Watches with Bethenny Frankel), and now brand builder. Introducing @parchiepal, the watch line created with kids in mind. Read all about Cara’s journey to design watches that are fun, affordable, and easy to use at the link in bio.

node.text:
Update: SOLD. The site has confirmed the sale of the piece for $7.63 million, setting the record for most expensive wristwatch made by an independent watchmaker sold publicly. 

 A Collected Man is offering this Grande et Petite Sonnerie by Philippe Dufour, the third of only eight examples produced, and the only piece to feature a rose gold case and white enamel dial. Completed in 1995, it was first delivered to the Sultan of Brunei. If sold, the piece is expected to set a new world record for the most expensive watch made by an independent watchmaker.

node.text: “From almost any angle, this watch does it for me. I love the size, the grip on the bezel, the excellent lume, and the no-fuss layout. It is both functional and representative of Seiko’s history of making dive watches…all while being quite subtle and easy to wear.” @jestacey looks back on his year with the Seiko Prospex SPB143 at the link in bio.
